						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Sik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Supposedly in NTSC black should be 16 and white should be 235. No idea from where the hell this comes (blacker than black and whiter than white are used for blanking signals but no sane video encoder should allow those for normal colors for starters), but that's the gist of it.</div><br />Well, <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YCbCr">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YCbCr</a><!-- m -->, for starters; neither values of 16 nor 235 are far enough away from 0 and 255 to be able to also encode sync nor Y+C (140IRE) in band.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

